tions with little concern for where they might appear next. In their attacks on sex workers and trans people, the more reactionary branches of this feminist movement play into the hands of the resurgent far-right.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aWhite feminism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  a#MeToo.  aCapitalism.  aColonialism.  aFar right.  aFeminism.  aMedia.  aRace.  aRape.  aSexual harrassment.  aTransgender.1 aPhipps, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615272540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526152725423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526152725/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles